description.narrative: The continuum of services was provided to children in both humanitarian and development settings. Child Protection Community Mechanisms have been reinforced to prevent and respond to violence and child marriages and promote births registration. Adolescents aged between 10-19 years continued to participate in life skills activities to be able to prevent violence, child marriage and risky behaviors. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/06/2020
